# Bot File Structure

## Core Bot Files
- `bot.py` - Main entry point for the bot
- `config.py` - Configuration settings and environment variables
- `handlers/` - Directory containing command and message handlers
  - `command_handlers.py` - Handles bot commands
  - `callback_handlers.py` - Handles callback queries
  - `message_handlers.py` - Handles text messages

## User Management
- `models/user.py` - User data model
- `services/user_service.py` - User management logic
- `controllers/user_controller.py` - User-related bot interactions

## Payment System
- `services/payment_service.py` - Payment processing logic
- `integrations/crypto_pay_api.py` - Crypto Pay API integration
- `models/transaction.py` - Transaction data model

## Product Management
- `models/product.py` - Product data model
- `services/product_service.py` - Product catalog and purchase logic
- `controllers/product_controller.py` - Product-related bot interactions

## Database
- `db/database.py` - Database connection and setup
- `db/repositories/` - Data access layer
  - `user_repository.py` - User data operations
  - `transaction_repository.py` - Transaction data operations
  - `product_repository.py` - Product data operations
